Fred Hatch was battered to death with a claw hammer by his neighbour Alan Rogers, 73 . 
  Rogers was sentenced to a hospital order under the Mental Health Act and told he may never be released . 
  Mr Hatch, 76, had bought his wife Enid 50 yellow roses for their golden wedding anniversary . 
  He was killed two months later after he smashed his skull with a hammer . 
  Enid Hatch said the memory of the horrific attack will 'stay with me for ever' Rogers was suffering from paranoid schizophrenia at the time of the attack . 
  Mrs Hatch's sister Betty was murdered in 1971 . 
 